CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier, May 29, 1965, pg. 6 reads: "Stunning Clubwomen - Taking part in the Lilac Tea activities at Bethesda Presbyterian Church, May 16, were members of the host group, the Homewood-Brushton Civic Club. Pictured are Rosalee Johnson, Rachel Irwin and Esther Hodges.  Other members include the president, Carmen Boddy; Arlene Bivens, Saphronia Collington, Henrietta Guin, Laura Johnson, Maud Marshall, Romaine Moore, Susann McCoy, Mary Nesbit, Roxie Brown, Bessie Powell Ollie Royal, Josephine Walker, Ollie Finney and Anna Harris. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Homewood-Brushton Civic Club members Rosalee Johnson, Rachel Irwin and Esther Hodges, standing behind table for Lilac Tea at Bethesda Presbyterian Church
